In the summer of 1978, 8 staff photographers for The NYT were idled by a strike at the city’s newspapers. So a group of them wandered the city, taking photos of the city's parks — and the people in them.

6 months ago, a parks official found the pictures. Here are some of our favorites: https://nyti.ms/2HBg0qI
